Class VoiceChatClient

java.lang.Object
com.audiostreaming.VoiceChatClient
public class VoiceChatClient extends Object
Voice chat client that manages TCP control channel and UDP audio streaming.

Handles connection to the server, registration, audio capture/playback, and state management (mute, join/leave).

    • leaveCall

      public void leaveCall()
      Leave the audio call but keep the TCP control channel connected. This allows the user to "Leave Call" and later "Join Call" quickly without reconnecting to TCP.

    • disconnect

      public void disconnect()
      Fully disconnect from the server: send LEAVE and close TCP, stop audio and monitor.
